1. Introduction

Jammu is a rapidly developing urban area where efficient management of traffic, air quality, and waste collection is important for improving citizen services.
An IoT-based smart city system can use connected sensors, wireless communication, cloud platforms, and dashboards to monitor city resources in real time.
This proposal focuses on three areas:

Smart Street Lighting
Smart Parking Management
Smart Air Quality Monitoring
1. Smart Street Lighting System
Objective

Automatically control street lights based on environmental conditions and vehicle/pedestrian movement to reduce electricity consumption.

Sensors Required
LDR sensor – Detects day/night conditions
PIR sensor – Detects pedestrian or vehicle movement
Current sensor – Monitors power consumption
Hardware
ESP32 microcontroller
LDR sensor
PIR sensor
Relay/MOSFET driver
LED street light model
Connectivity
Wi-Fi / LoRaWAN
MQTT protocol for data transmission

Light Sensor + PIR Sensor
          |
          ↓
        ESP32
          |
       MQTT
          |
          ↓
     Cloud Server
          |
          ↓
 Smart City Dashboard

Working

During daytime, lights remain OFF. At night, lights operate at low brightness. 
When motion is detected, brightness increases automatically.
The system reduces unnecessary power usage.

