Security Considerations
Use HTTPS/TLS encryption for cloud communication.
Store device credentials securely.
Use MQTT authentication.
Update ESP32 firmware regularly.
Avoid storing passwords directly in source code.
Conclusion

The proposed IoT-based smart city system can help Jammu improve energy efficiency, reduce traffic problems, and monitor environmental conditions. 
Smart street lighting can reduce electricity waste, smart parking can improve traffic flow, and air quality monitoring can help authorities take timely action.
Using ESP32 nodes, MQTT communication, and cloud dashboards provides a scalable and cost-effective solution suitable for future smart city development.

Estimated Deployment Cost:

Street Lighting Node: ~₹1200/node
Parking Node: ~₹900/node
Air Quality Node: ~₹2300/node

The system can be expanded in the future by adding smart water management, waste monitoring, and public safety applications.
